Eee! Keep scrubbing
right there.

262
00:15:54,750 --> 00:15:57,458
As you command.

263
00:15:57,541 --> 00:16:00,666
[KIRIHA] Your hands
feel enormous.

264
00:16:00,750 --> 00:16:03,041
[KAZUYA] That's only
because you're smaller.

265
00:16:03,125 --> 00:16:04,958
I wonder what else
seems bigger now.

266
00:16:05,041 --> 00:16:08,125
[KAZUYA]
You are such a pervert.

267
00:16:08,208 --> 00:16:09,916
[KIRIHA giggles]

268
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:13,166
I meant the tub, of course!
It's like a pool in here.

269
00:16:13,250 --> 00:16:15,541
You're splashing
water everywhere.

270
00:16:15,625 --> 00:16:18,208
I'll stop...

271
00:16:22,291 --> 00:16:23,041
[KIRIHA]
Hmm...

272
00:16:23,125 --> 00:16:25,875
[KAZUYA]
Let me wield you.

273
00:16:25,958 --> 00:16:28,625
Spiral Weave! Layered Edge!

274
00:16:30,833 --> 00:16:33,375
[KIRIHA] The eight-layered
Spiral Weave.

275
00:16:33,458 --> 00:16:36,375
That was Kanaka's technique.

276
00:16:44,458 --> 00:16:46,458
[KANAKA]
Say, Kiriha.

277
00:16:46,541 --> 00:16:48,250
[KIRIHA]
Mm?

278
00:16:48,333 --> 00:16:49,625
[KANAKA]
If anything...

279
00:16:49,708 --> 00:16:52,833
Hypothetically, if anything
happened to me...

280
00:16:52,916 --> 00:16:54,750
Would you take care of Kazuya?

281
00:16:54,833 --> 00:16:56,750
[KIRIHA]
Ha! Don't be ridiculous.

282
00:16:56,833 --> 00:17:00,458
You're way too tough
to worry about that.

283
00:17:00,541 --> 00:17:03,208
No, then?

284
00:17:03,291 --> 00:17:06,250
This is an absurd line
of thinking, but fine.

285
00:17:06,333 --> 00:17:09,041
Should you be killed,
I'll keep him safe.

286
00:17:09,125 --> 00:17:12,000
[KANAKA]
Kiriha.

287
00:17:12,083 --> 00:17:14,541
Thank you.

288
00:17:14,625 --> 00:17:16,083
[KIRIHA]
Right.

289
00:17:18,166 --> 00:17:19,375
[KIRIHA]
Kazuya.

290
00:17:19,458 --> 00:17:20,875
[KAZUYA]
Ah?

291
00:17:20,958 --> 00:17:24,500
[KIRIHA] I'll always
keep... you sa...

292
00:17:26,333 --> 00:17:28,125
[KAZUYA screams]

293
00:17:31,458 --> 00:17:34,500
[KIRIHA sighs]
Such a terrible blunder.

294
00:17:34,583 --> 00:17:35,583
[KAZUYA chuckles]

295
00:17:35,666 --> 00:17:39,583
Kazuya. I fear I am done for.

296
00:17:39,666 --> 00:17:42,875
Nah, you're just dizzy.
Too much time in the water.

297
00:17:42,958 --> 00:17:45,500
Pudding. One last
pudding before--

298
00:17:45,583 --> 00:17:47,250
Yeah, I'm not fallin' for it.

299
00:17:47,333 --> 00:17:49,500
Pudding...

300
00:17:54,208 --> 00:17:56,875
[KASUMI]
Huh? Old clothes... of mine?

301
00:17:56,958 --> 00:18:00,375
[KAZUYA] Yeah. Just on the off
chance you still have some.

302
00:18:01,875 --> 00:18:05,291
Like from when you were a little
less than half your height?

303
00:18:05,375 --> 00:18:07,791
Whatever do you
need them for?

304
00:18:07,875 --> 00:18:11,833
Well, uh...
Ya see, I...

305
00:18:11,916 --> 00:18:13,416
No, it can't be true.

306
00:18:13,500 --> 00:18:14,958
[KAZUYA]
Eh?

307
00:18:16,083 --> 00:18:17,583
[KASUMI]
You haven't...

308
00:18:17,666 --> 00:18:20,791
...discovered that you're
into that sort of thing?

309
00:18:20,875 --> 00:18:23,833
--[KAZUYA] Eh?
--You can't do this to me!

310
00:18:23,916 --> 00:18:27,291
You'll find naught but pain
and suffering down that path!

311
00:18:27,375 --> 00:18:28,416
[KASUMI gasps]

312
00:18:28,500 --> 00:18:29,916
[KASUMI] This could
be my last chance.

313
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:33,083
I must demonstrate the charm
and allure of older women.

314
00:18:33,166 --> 00:18:36,166
I must grasp his
heart and squeeze!

315
00:18:36,250 --> 00:18:39,333
Come to me, brother!
I'm ready as always!

316
00:18:39,416 --> 00:18:42,666
[KAZUYA] Never mind. Sorry
to interrupt your cooking.

317
00:18:42,750 --> 00:18:44,083
[KASUMI]
Huh?

318
00:18:44,166 --> 00:18:46,041
[KASUMI screams]

319
00:18:47,375 --> 00:18:50,333
[CHISATO] Old clothes?
I might still have some,

320
00:18:50,416 --> 00:18:52,958
but I doubt I can get
them to you tonight.

321
00:18:53,041 --> 00:18:55,500
[KAZUYA] I figured as much.
Thanks anyway.

322
00:18:55,583 --> 00:18:56,625
[CHISATO]
Yeah, of course.

323
00:18:56,708 --> 00:18:58,916
I'll let you know if
I find something.

324
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:01,958
That would be great.
I'll see ya later.

325
00:19:04,833 --> 00:19:07,791
Hm. I guess she could wear
some of my old clothes,

326
00:19:07,875 --> 00:19:09,833
if I can find any.

327
00:19:28,416 --> 00:19:29,625
[OSAMU]
I've brought them.

328
00:19:29,708 --> 00:19:31,166
[KAZUYA gasps]

329
00:19:33,583 --> 00:19:35,458
[KAZUYA]
Osamu.

330
00:19:35,541 --> 00:19:37,583
[OSAMU]
The items you requested.

331
00:19:39,750 --> 00:19:41,333
[KAZUYA]
Thanks.

332
00:19:41,416 --> 00:19:46,000
Sorry for springing this on you.
I appreciate it.

333
00:19:46,083 --> 00:19:48,166
[OSAMU] You took
me by surprise,

334
00:19:48,250 --> 00:19:53,083
but I won't question why you
might desire such clothes.

335
00:19:53,166 --> 00:19:56,416
That isn't my place, and we
all have our inner shadows

336
00:19:56,500 --> 00:19:59,000
that we keep hidden from
the world, don't we?

337
00:19:59,083 --> 00:20:01,625
[KAZUYA] Please stop.
You have no idea, man.

338
00:20:05,083 --> 00:20:08,750
Ah! Well done, Kazuya!
Now give them here.

339
00:20:08,833 --> 00:20:10,500
You've brought
me pudding, yes?

340
00:20:10,583 --> 00:20:14,875
Oh, yeah. I did, but that
isn't what I went out for.

341
00:20:14,958 --> 00:20:19,041
Here. I borrowed some outfits
that should be around your size.

342
00:20:19,125 --> 00:20:21,666
You can't go out
wearing just my t-shirts,

343
00:20:21,750 --> 00:20:25,500
and I'd feel bad making you stay
in obi form all the time, so...

344
00:20:25,583 --> 00:20:29,208
Ha! How considerate!
You're finally starting

345
00:20:29,291 --> 00:20:32,833
to think like a servant.
I'm proud of you.

346
00:20:32,916 --> 00:20:34,541
[KIRIHA giggles]

347
00:20:34,625 --> 00:20:36,541
[KIRIHA growls]

348
00:20:36,625 --> 00:20:38,083
[KAZUYA]
Huh?

349
00:20:40,625 --> 00:20:42,458
[KIRIHA]
Kazuya?

350
00:20:44,166 --> 00:20:47,791
[KIRIHA] Of all the
clothes in the world...

351
00:20:47,875 --> 00:20:50,125
[KIRIHA] Why would
you choose...

352
00:20:50,208 --> 00:20:51,625
...these?!

353
00:20:51,708 --> 00:20:54,291
Yeah. I got this
bag from Osamu

354
00:20:54,375 --> 00:20:56,916
and didn't think to look
inside till just now.

355
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:59,541
This Osamu...
The one with glasses?

356
00:20:59,625 --> 00:21:01,625
What on earth do
you think he is?

357
00:21:01,708 --> 00:21:03,166
Not sure.

358
00:21:03,250 --> 00:21:06,916
He said these were reference
materials for his manga.

359
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:10,791
I'm not even sure that this
one qualifies as clothing.

360
00:21:10,875 --> 00:21:12,291
It's nothing but string.

361
00:21:12,375 --> 00:21:13,791
Damn it.

362
00:21:13,875 --> 00:21:17,166
Well, hopefully at least a few
of these will be wearable.

363
00:21:17,250 --> 00:21:20,333
So, which of these garments
best suits your predilections?

364
00:21:20,416 --> 00:21:21,958
If you truly want
me to wear one,

365
00:21:22,041 --> 00:21:25,500
I'm sure we can
work something out.

366
00:21:25,583 --> 00:21:27,083
[KAZUYA]
Nope, I'm good.

367
00:21:27,166 --> 00:21:28,833
[KIRIHA giggles]
There's no need to be coy.

368
00:21:28,916 --> 00:21:31,250
Seriously, please don't do this.

369
00:21:36,666 --> 00:21:37,708
Kazuya.

370
00:21:37,791 --> 00:21:39,791
[KAZUYA]
Hey, Osamu. How goes it?

371
00:21:41,416 --> 00:21:43,750
Did you enjoy
yourself last night?

372
00:21:43,833 --> 00:21:45,583
[KAZUYA]
Huh? Yeah, I...

373
00:21:45,666 --> 00:21:48,750
Ohh! No. N-N...
Look, Osamu.

374
00:21:48,833 --> 00:21:51,416
Th-That w-wa--
Hiss 'n' leer, man.

375
00:21:51,500 --> 00:21:53,208
[CHISATO] What's this
about hissing, Kazuya?

376
00:21:53,291 --> 00:21:55,500
--[KAZUYA] It's nothing.
--[CHISATO] How suspicious.

377
00:21:55,583 --> 00:21:57,166
[KAZUYA]
It really is nothing!

378
00:23:27,958 --> 00:23:30,000
[KAZUYA] I've taken on the
position of malison cleanser,

379
00:23:30,083 --> 00:23:32,833
so Kiriha begins to teach
me how to wield an obi.

380
00:23:32,916 --> 00:23:36,750
But before I can learn much,
another Amasogi appears.

381
